African education ministers have recommended improved teacher training, curriculum review, better funding and gender equality to boost standards on the continent. The Pan African High-Level Conference that ended on Friday came up with the “Nairobi Declaration”. It calls on African countries to focus more on Technical Vocational Educational Training to enhance skills in Sciences, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM). President Uhuru Kenyatta who officially closed the summit emphasised the need for partnerships between governments in implementing the declaration.